Text: Fittingly, Gibson finds Mickle. Johnny Bravo are champs for the first time ever. 13-11 your final.
Neff over the top to Garcia. Bravo 12-11 Ironside. Game point o for Bravo
Pure d-line out there for Bravo.
Smith scores from Mickle. Bravo 12-10 Ironside
Bravo with it on the goal line. Brodie on the cone.
Stubbs to Foster for the goal. Pretty throw. Bravo 11-10 Ironside
RT @kdubsultimate: If we are going to cap every game, why not make them timed? Easier for fans to understand. @USAUltimate
Forshee scoober for Lance into the endzone. Bravo 11-9 Ironside. Soft cap is on. Game to 13
Lokke with a d for Bravo
Muffin with the disc at the brick.
Farrell with a blade for Keegan and Bravo finish out this long. But, there's another stoppage. The score stands. Bravo 10-9 Ironside.
Gibson gets a run through.
Herscu off, Cricket on for Ironside.
Watson misses Kloor. Kloor injured. Mcshane comes in.
Stubbs misses on the break chance. Bravo O with another shot to hold.
Cricket scores for Ironside. Bravo 9-9 Ironside
Brodie scores from Gibson. Bravo 9-8 Ironside
Bravo take a timeout to give their o line a break.
Gibson saves the point with the tip. Bravo trying to get a hold.
Mickle turns it over.
Wallack comes in for John Stubbs as Ironside look to break. Stubbs special to Babbitt gets block by Morgan.
Muffin to Piers for the score. Ironside 8-8 Bravo #nationalsTX
Bravo give it back. Muffin with the disc.
Ryan Farrell with a bidding block.
...or if McCarthy sent them on to give his offense some help on the turn.
Krier said last night that Bravo was looking to force GOAT to mix up their lines.  Not sure if Stubbs and Babbitt switch was purposeful...
Mickle and Gibson joining Lance there on that D point, with Kloor coming in on the injury sub. Krier using his offense to convert the break.
Gibson scores from Lance. Lance and Mickle just took over for Bravo's offense there. Bravo 8-7 Ironside. That's the half. #NationalsTX
Watson to Ackley for the score. Ironside 7-7 Bravo. Bravo calls timeout here and will come out looking to get the second break back for half
Stubbs and Babbitt were both on the o line for that last point. They both return for this d point for Ironside.
Stubbs for Foster in the endzone. Ironside 7-6 Bravo.
Bravo D get it back and Peterson makes an appearance in the endzone on the end of the McShane hammer. Ironside 6-6 Bravo.
Hank Conker bodies up for the D and McShane calls timeout. Bravo looking to get one of the two breaks back.
Watson to Kloor. Ironside 6-5 Bravo.
Muffin finds Brian Garcia for the score. Ironside 6-4 Bravo
Lance gets the D but Danny Clark snags it back
Mickle to R. Farrell for the score. Ironside 5-4 Bravo.
Ironside BREAK. Wallack to Simmons. Ironside 2/2 on break chances. Ironside 5-3 Bravo
Keegan overthrows Gibson. Turnover.
Rebholz to Cricket for the score. Ironside in control so far, but Bravo not far away. Ironside 4-3 Bravo
Smith to Gibson for the goal. Ironside 3-3 Bravo
Babbitt shaking his head as he listens to Brodie. Upheld.
Babbitt Ds up Brodie. We have a call.
Easy Ironside O. Cricket slings one in for Danny Clark. Ironside 3-2 Bravo.
Gibson finds Mickle. Ironside 2-2 Bravo.
Mickle floats a huck too high and Stubbs with a counterstike to Babbitt. Break for Ironside. Ironside 2-1 Bravo
Kapinos was a huge presence on offense yesterday against Ring.
For those keeping track, Ironside's Alex Kapinos is on crutches on the sideline.
Muffin goes full field from a standstill to find Neff. Neff snags the assist. 1-1
To open the game, we see Mickle leap up and sky for the point. Bravo 1-0 Ironside
Johnston dishes to White on the move and Scandal take the game. Final score Scandal 12-10 Fury #nationalsTX
Disc goes back Mercier.
White standing waiting for observers to rule on what should be the game.
Hard cap is on.
Fury turn it at mid field.
Foul is overturned. Fury disc.
Payne calls a foul as o'connor tries to find her on a high stall.
O'Connor to pick up.
Fury injury and the clock has stopped.
These picks could be hurting Fury.
Excellent D from Fury as time continues to tick away.
5 minutes to hard cap.
Howard puts it in to Narayan for Fury. Scandal 11-10 Fury.
Travel called. Coming back for fury.
Howard tries her luck and draws a foul.
Foul called on the huck. It's uncontested and Romano will have it for Fury.
Scandal hang on to break and we have a game to 13. Scandal 11-9 Fury.
Opi being Opi. Horizontal D and an overruled foul call.
Fury have a wide open chance and miss the end zone again.
Payne with a throwaway.
Mercier takes a timeout. Scandal are a few yards away from a crucial break. Fury need a big stand. #nationalsTX
Ruden turfs it for Fury.
Soft cap horn blows. We'll add 2 at the end of the point.
O'Connor putting up a big floater to Jorgensen for a Scandal break. Scandal 10-9 Fury.
< 3 minutes until cap
Opi bombs it to a steaking Daly. Scandal hold. Fury 9-9 Scandal.
Turnover for scandal followed by one from Fury where they miss the endzone by a few feet. Scandal back with it.
Opi out on offense for Scandal
That's a Fury break. Two straight for them out of half. #nationalsTX
Fury's Duffy with a big d to create a short field opportunity
That is Fury's second completed huck this game.
Snyder finds Chow for a Fury hold. Scandal 8-8 Fury
Fury working on O to start this half.
Opi breaks to White and breaks for half! Scandal leads fury 8-7. #NationalsTX
Sneider injured on the play for Fury, but walks off the field. A fury drop gives scandal a chance at a break.
Mercier upline to O Conner for the 7-7 tie. Next point for half! #NationalsTX
Fury holds on offense despite tight scandal defense. Desmond with a great throw to Ruden. Fury leads 7-6.
RT @aint_so_bad: @USAUltimate @Ultiworldlive was #6 on scandal evaluated for a concussion after that knee to the head? #shouldbe
Fury over throws their receiver, and Scandal takes advantage with a Break! Opi with the score. Tied at 6-6.
Fury and Scandal exchange posessions, but DC shows a level head and puts it in on offense. 6-5 Fury leads.
Fury with great cutting and the easy score. 6-4 SF over DC in the women's final. #NationalsTX
Scandal gets the disc back on a deep d. Opi finds White for the offensive hold. DC still trails 5-4.
Fury takes a time out with a break chance. They lead 5-3.
Jorgensen with a huge end zone D for Fury. Fury gets a chance at their 3rd straight break.
Duffy with D for Fury. They find Nazarov for their second straight break! SF up 5-3.
The Fury zone forces a turn and a short field. The late stall hammer from Narayan leads to a fury break. 4-3 SF leads.
Scandal very Poachy in their defense. Fury stagnant offensively. They eventually find Nazarov in the end zone for the offensive hold. 3's.
Opi hucks to Beach, to score the DC break! Beautiful throw. 3-2.
Patient O from DC, until a completed high stall huck from Johnston. Tied at 2's. #NationalsTX
Scandal turns and Snyder finds Fletcher for the Fury break. SF leads 2-1.
Scandal with their first turn of the game, and now SF has a chance to break. They try the huck but Johnston with the D for Scandal.
6 turns this point total. Fury finds Lisa P in the end zone for the eventual hold. Scandal with three break chances that point. 1-1.
Fury with the ill advised huck leading to the Scandal D. Scandal can't take advantage with the disc. SF back on O.
SF Fury with the pull. Scandal with smooth offense and the hold. 1-0 start with DC on told. Mercier with the assist.
And that's it! Drag N Thrust wins on a goal to Meckstroth. 15-9 final.
Seattle gets their first break of the game on a deep shot to Dominic Cavalero. 14-9 DNT
After the timeout, five total turns by both teams until Bailey catches a nice huck from Burton. 14-8, DNT receiving for the win.
Seattle turns it, DNT calls a timeout. Need to work full field for the break.
14-7 Drag N Thrust one point away
Cam Bailey with a huge scoober and Burton with the nice grab for the goal, but Seattle still behind 13-7.
Meckstroth to Clark for the goal. 13-6, DNT two points away from victory.
Cameron Bailey with goal for Seattle. They trail DNT 12-6.
Another easy o point for DNT and they lead 12-5
Seattle scores. 11-5 Drag N Thrust leads.
11-4 Drag N Thrust
Drag N Thrust with another break. This one is turning into a blowout. Up 10-4 over Seattle
9-5 DNT. They score easily out of half.
After turner by both teams, DNT holds. They lead at half 8-4 over Ghetto Birds
Ghetto Birds hold on offense. Johnson to Paul. 7-4 Drag N' Thrust up.
Burton can't hit Johnson deep. DNT capitalizes again on a huck to Brian Schoenrock for the break. DNT up 7-3, pulling for half.
Silly throw by Cameron Bailey 5yds out of the end zone gives DNT the disc. They break in three throws. 6-3 Drag N Thrust leads.
Uncontested foul in the end zone gives Drag N Thrust the goal. They're up 5-3
Burton to Paul. 4-3 DNT
DNT works it up the field and scores on an easy upline to Austin Lien for the 4-2 lead. drag n thrust is the better team so far.
Seattle gets the turn, but a bad throw to Khaleef in the end zone gives it right back to DNT.
Phil Paul of Ghetto catches a long throw right outside the end zone and calls a TO. Out of the timeout, easy goal to Burton. 3-2 DNT
DNT with another break. Mike Petersen to Sarah Anciaux. 3-1 DNT, up two breaks early.
Another throwaway from Seattle offense. DNT with the disc 20 yards out.
Bad unforced throwaway off the pull from Seattle leads to a Drag N Thrust break. 2-1 DNT
After turns by both team, Austin Lien throws a monster full field bomb to James Hron for the Drag N Thrust goal. 1-1
Ghetto Birds immediately huck deep to Mark Burton, who pulls it down and throws the short goal to Phil Paul. 1-0 Seattle
Mixed finals about to begin. Seattle receiving on offense.
Gibson with 7 goals. Unreal.
Farrell finishes a patient Bravo possession with an OI backhand to the back corner for Gibson. Bravo is headed to the final.
Double season point, folks.
GOAT works the other way and, after a Toly layout, score on Toly to Carroll.
Observers say no foul.
Mickle gets up and calls the foul. Crowd not a fan.
Mickle upline and he and Hibbert both bid. Looks like a turn but Mickle lands on his shoulder. Injury timeout.
Bravo TMF btw.
Lindquist has been exceptional in this game. Extremely reliable.
Foord diving catch saves possession. Nice break throw to Lindquist who jumps it in. 13-12, Bravo can hold to win.
Bravo being very strategic. Junk to take GOAT out of pull play, heavy switching to contain deep cuts.
Patient Bravo D line offense weathers a few mistakes there and get a break. GOAT O has to be gassed. 13-11, Bravo.
Peterson can't put weight on it. Gibson comes in, Carroll for GOAT.
Lloyd with a close bid, Peterson goes down trying to dodge him after the catch. Injury stoppage.
Lloyd with a huck to Harris but Harris looks away before the throw and finds it too late. Conker D.
Observers say they didn't see it and send it back. Seen too many send backs today.
Lindquist with a big flick huck to Harris. Petersen flies in for another highlight reel help D over the top. Foul call.
Another back line pull from Bravo gives GOAT a long way to go.
A massive Brodie flick huck to Gibson hangs. Keegan catches the trash. 12-11, game to 14.
Stall 9 scoober from Lindquist finds Masek-Kelly on the break side. Total punt. GOAT goal. Nichols goal. 11-11, a minute till cap.
Jimmy freakin Mickle. Insane layout grab on a Watson huck. Dishes to Gibson for his 6th goal. "Way to extend my range!" cheers Watson.
Easy Hibbert to Ojo red zone goal. What a way to give up the break. Back to 10s.
Morgan loses the disc faking and catches it again. Ruled a turnover. Incredibly strange.
Lindquist hammer to Yearwood after Lloyd overshoots a huck and Lokke drops one short. 10-9, Bravo. GOAT lateral throws excellent.
Deep shot to Lloyd against Petersen is just a little too floaty. McShane deep to a leaping Conker for a huge break. 10-8, Bravo.
Yet another set of GOAT legs thrown at Mickle. A huge loopy flick to Gibson, his fifth goal. Incredible touch and vision on the throw. 9-8.
Vasilyev to Martin with a hammer for the break. 8-8. Technical was for swearing.
Powell with a big layout D attempt. Takes an injury. Bravo gets a third technical foul and GOAT gets premium field position.
GOAT with a series of push passes up the open side to score, Lindquist to McKnight. 8-7, Bravo leads.
Huge break to take half! Bravo's Henry Konker with a great grab. 8-6
We're gonna stop updating Twitter and do everything in liveblog: http://ultiworld.com/2014/10/18/ultiworlds-club-championships-liveblog-presented-savage-ultimate/
GOAT gets the break! 5-5.
Kloor throws it away on a dump miscommunication right at the doorstep. GOAT takes timeout.
Lefty backhand from Justin Foord for the Thomson Mcknight score. 5-4 Bravo up a break
RT @PrideofNY: What we dared dream has actually come true: Tim Morrissey's hair looks even better than it did at college nationals.
Mark Lloyd dime huck to Karl Loiseau. 3-3
Bravo huck is too far and GOAT gets it back
GOAT huck is too far. Mark Lloyd tries for the greatest but it doesn't connect
Bravo holds to make it 3-2. Goat had a shot at a break after a nice D by Andrew Carroll, but they gave it right back
Goat ties it up. 2-2. Follow live on the liveblog: http://ultiworld.com/2014/10/18/ultiworlds-club-championships-liveblog-presented-savage-ultimate/
Bravo up 2-1 on GOAT after three offensive holds. No turnovers yet.
IRONSIDE WINS. Amazing defensive effort from Ring tonight. A very exciting, but extremely call heavy game.
Shane Sisco with the Ring takeaway
Ring another impressive defensive stand. Ironside working.
She had hops, but the fences here at the FC Dallas complex are pretty tall. A for the run, C- for the dismount.
And we're treated to a female streaker during this injury timeout.
Muffin calls timeout.
Nethercutt crushes cricket trying to make an upline. Injury called.
Kapinos is hanging onto his Ironside teammates as they discuss the call. The throw is being sent back.
Foul called after a ring huck gets tipped away by Ironside.
Ironside turns it on the goal line. Ring with a chance.
Ring take a timeout and send a few subs running along the sidelines getting the crowd to join them in booing Ring.
Christian Johnson ROOFS it to send this game to DGP. 12-12
Garcia to Clark and Ironside get their first point since 11-6. It is now Ironside 12-11 Ring.
Great stand from Ring so far. Ironside still working
Shane Sisco scores the BREAK. Tie ball game.
Stubbs and Babbitt both over from D line, but Stubbs throws it away.
Noah Saul pulls it out of bounds for Ring.
Justin Allen with a very big grab over Garcia. Ironside not looking as composed as they did earlier. Ironside 11-10 Ring
Two more turns since our last tweet. Ring with the disc.
Will Neff earns it back with a big D.  Muffin turns it.
Neff overthrows Cricket.
Ring is 3 for 4 on break conversions. Ironside is 6 for 7.
Justin Allen with a very big grab for ring. Ironside 11-9  Ring.
Ring looking to break again.
A force out foul is called after Dan Kantor reels in a big huck.
Kapinos looking for Clark turns it over.
Noah Saul with an enthusiastic spike after Ring pick up a break. Ironside 11-8 Ring. Soft cap horn blows. We'll add 2 after this point.
Danny Clark throwaway.
Ironside 11-7 Ring. Ken Porter scores. 2 and a half minutes to soft cap.
Ironside is 6 of 7 on break conversions.
Ironside score on a high release from Simmons to Hatchett. Ironside 11-6.
Jeff Babbitt chases down a big backhand from Stubbs. Ironside timeout at goal line. C. Johnson with the pivotal drop for ring in endzone.
Cricket gets the flip from Neff after Neff's foul call is upheld. Ironside 10-6 Ring
The call is overturned. Ring get a break. Ironside 9-6 Ring. #nationalsTX
A giant Tristan Green huck comes back on a pick call.
Ironside 9-5 Ring. Noah Saul on the score from Bode.
Quella to Ingolds-Smith for an Ironside break. Ironside 9-4 Ring.
Ring open with a turnover.
George has now thrown for break scores. Hatchett scores this one for Ironside 8-4.
Impressive Cricket scoober finds Danny Clark.  Ironside 7-4 Ring.
Ironside 6-4 Ring.
Ironside pick up another break. George Stubbs has thrown three break scores, Ironside 3-4 on converting breaks. Ironside 6-3 Ring
Garcia to Neff for the Ironside score. Ironside 5-3 Ring. Long, long point. #nationalsTX
Justin Allen heavily involved in this point for Ring. He has a interception, a drop, has drawn a pick call.
Ring find the break. Sisco scores. Ironside 4-3 Ring.
Noah Saul calls timeout for Ring. They'll huddle up and try to come up with something to find their first break.
Cricket with a stone cold drop
Green to Bowen for the Ring score. Big throw from Green. Ironside 4-2 Ring #nationalsTX
Tristan Green drops a low pass for Ring. Ironside with another chance to break.
Stubbs finds Sidorsky for the Ironside break. That's Ironside 4-1 Ring. Two breaks in the first five points. #nationalsTX
Christian Johnson picks up George Stubbs for a mark.
Micah Hood launches a big flick upwind that sails out of bounds. Ironside pick up.
Wallack on Nethercutt.
George to John Stubbs. Rookie John with a monster grab for an upwind Ironside break. Ironside 3-1 Ring
Ken Porter of Ring marking G. Stubbs of Ironside.
Nethercutt turnover.
Ironside 2-1 Ring. In serve #nationalsTX
Lisa P's throw misses her intended target, but Daryani cleans up the trash, Fury win 12-10 and advance the to Finals to face Scandal
Riot makes two tough catches that point. O'Malley with the score for Seattle. 11-10 Fury. Game point on offense for Fury
Fury finds a wide open Narayan for the score. 11-9 SF
Riot gets a layout D from Craley, but a huck from Mercer goes way too far. Fury with the disc
Great touch flick from O'Malley. 10-9 Fury, game to 12.
Soft cap horn just blew, teams will complete the point.
Patient offense. Lots of handler movement for Fury, Lisa P. with the score. 10-8 Fury
Turn from Fury near their own goal line leads to a Riot easy score. 9-8 Fury leads
Lockdown defense by Fury, Riot has to punt
Fury gets the D back from Duffy, Nazarov up the line for the score. 9-7 Fury, soft cap in eight minutes.
Nazarov's huck too far, Riot with the disc
Patient O from Fury, Nazarov to Finney for a San Francisco break. Fury up 8-7, receiving out of half
Fury throws a junk zone, drop from Riot.
Fury easily breaks through the Riot zone. Romano finds Desmond wide open in the end zone. 7-7. Riot receiving
Riot gets a D on a questionable huck, super patient offense, McDowell to McKibben for a Riot break. 7-6 Riot, game on serve.
Titcomb with a great around flick for the offensive hold. The crowd looks on in amazement. Tied at 6.
Jorgensen gets another fury D! Fury fails to convert. They're getting turns on a 3 person zone but can't convert. Riot with a chance.
2 straight breaks for Fury. They lead 6-5 over Riot.
Fury can't take advantage of the break chance. But Riot gets it back. After another turn Furys Narayan throws a big huck for a break.
Narayan with the heads up D for Fury. They get a chance to break.
Jorgensen to Duffy for the Fury break score! Tied with Riot 5 all. Great composure from the Fury D line.
Riot can't punch it in after beating the zone. Fury with a chance to get the break back.
This semis match between Riot and Fury feels like a finals. One of the best crowds so far.
Two great grabs from Fury's Lisa P. She scores for the San Francisco offensive hold. 5-4 riot leads.
Riot gets an easy poach D. Johnson with a big break flick to Titcomb for the break. Riot leads 5-3.
Two turns. Riot floating some throws downwind. Some great catches on their second chance.  Kawai scores to hold serve. 4-3 Riot.
Pretty flick from midfield Snyder to Laroche for the goal. 3 all. Riot to receive. Riot missed a big chance with a fumble near the goalline
Itoh hucks to White for the game winning goal. 15-7. Another scandal blowout semis win.
Big drop from Stern. Fury gets another chance on offense.
Massive layout d from Riots Kelly Johnson!
Hoffmann gets a d and catches a blading huck not intended for her. Titcomb to Baecher for the first Boston break. 14-7.
Fury gets the disc but bad injury. Sarah "surge" Griffith down.
Takes a few tries Malinowski hits Groom for 14-6.
Riot throws a 3-3-1 wall zone. Slows Fury down but they still work through it until they drop. Riot gets a chance but turnover a floater
Big bladey backhand from Fontenette to Cardenas in a crowd. Excellent catch.  Goal. 3-2 Riot up and pulling
Very high tempo from both teams. Riot going horizontal. A few higher stalls but they get to the endzone line.
Easy and casual Scandal O point. Just score to make it game point in the semis. No big deal. 14-5.
High stall Chang punt and Chelsea Murphy yanks it down. 13-5.
Timeout Fury. They will pull. Possibly loading up a D line.
Some really nice throws from Fury. Desmond scores again. Still movin very fast but keep the last drive mistake free. 2-2.
Lots of turns. Both teams going fast and making mistakes.
Franke with an easy D and Mercier sends it to Beach. Her 3rd goal, 13-4.
Nice backhand huck from Jorgenson. Desmond solid snag. Outside the endzone. Two stoppages. Stall called and upheld on goal line
Not much resistance. Opi to Itoh for 12-4, all Scandal.
McDowell to Mercer for the goal. Nice big backhand break. Score is 2-1 Riot back on serve
Tunnell has been going upfield against smaller handler defenders. Like the idea but Brute hasnt committed to it yet. Hasn't been targeted.
Miss from Nora Carr. Turn. But then a Fury drop. Bit sloppy this point.
Opi with an emphatic layout D. Emblematic of how few upfield options have existed for Boston.
Riot forces backhand with the wind. Fury going too fast, misconnect. Disc hits the ground.
Maddox Ds the predictable inside break but Scandal gives it back.
Big huck upwind and Riot swings and scores. Kingery gets the goal. Big hold. 1-1.
McClellan to Daly the other way. Both teams look like the game is over. 11-4, Scandal leads.
Foot block for Fury and then sick layout on a swing, but they turn it outside the endzone.
Murphy D gets Brute a chance. Baecher tosses a jump ball huck. Turn.
Early turn from Riot. Good pressure d. High stall shot from Fury about twenty yards out, Desmond with good grab for break. 1-0 Fury.
Boston two throw score, Hoffmann under and then backhand huck to Groom. 10-4, Scandal.
Riot v Fury. Riot to receive in north endzone. Wind coming in from the northeast
Even Brute's loaded line could not hold. D Line now on O.
Jorgensen takes an injury sub. Payne unleashes a bomb to rookie Laura Pape for 10-3.
Tunnell throws a break side huck to Malinowski and Jorgensen hauls to get to it first. Incredible D.
Baecher, Groom, Hoffmann all coming from D line to play this O point.
Maddox upline from Jorgensen. Scandal with dominant 9-3 lead.
Scandal gets a second D of the point. D line has just 2 turns and are playing extremely effective upfield D.
Brute goes to a split stack. Groom puts a backhand to space to Malinowski and Opi with a huge layout over the top. Foul call.
Brute throwaway and Scandal punches it in, Payne to Wickner in the back corner. 7-3, Scandal in commanding position. Scandal TO.
O'Connor boosts it to Itoh. Daly scores on a hammer from Mercier, the and-1 catch. 6-3, Scandal leads Brute.
Titcomb layout toe in attempt misses. Brute misses first break opportunity.
Sorry might be Ludford with the sky.
Call overruled. Baecher RIPS an upwind backhand and Groom goes over Roy for it. Lengthy call stoppage right now.
Mercier huck to Daly gets over her head but she calls the push in the back foul. Discussion ensuing.
Brute eats up the open side in an easy hold. 5-3.
Scandals offense looks unfazed. Itoh high release backhand to McClellan. 5-2.
Seville drops in a high stall fading backhand to Malinowski. Crucial hold, 4-2.
Chang drops the Payne downwind pull. Easy Maddux goal to Beach. 4-1. Brute has to bounce back.
Dump and swing sets up Jorgesen to Beach in front break corner. First blood goes to Scandal. 3-1.
Tunnell with a big endzone D but Seville drop gives Scandal a short field.
Scandal responds with an equally patient point against Brute matchup zone. 2-1 on serve.
Big upset as Seattle Mixed defeats Boston Wild Card 15-12 to advance to the title game. They'll play Drag'n Thrust tomorrow at 11 AM.
Patient offensive hold from Brute. Scandal defense working the handlers legs; Maddux/Tunnell matchup could have huge impact. 1-1.
Kahyee Fong with a HUGE SKY and then throws a two yard game winning goal to Burton. 15-12 Ghetto Birds over Wild Card. Seattle moves on.
Opening hold for Scandal, Daly beating Groom deep. Some poaching in the handler lanes from Brute. 1-0.
Wild Card holds. Ian Engler with the goal past a bidding Henry Phan. 14-12 Seattle.
Khaleef with a hammer to Evan Klein for the goal. 14-11 Ghetto Birds. Cap to 15, Seattle with four chances to close it.
Throw away by Shellie Cohen of Wild Card. ghetto works it to half field and calls a timeout.
Couple of turns, but then Cogburn comes down with a mac in the endzone for the break. 13-11, Seattle Mixed on the doorstep.
Burton layout goal and then Seattle D gets the break off a tipped disc. Goal by Cogbutn. 13-11 Ghetto Birds
Another errant throw, and Wild Card punch it in easy. 3-0 run by Boston ties it up at 11s.
Seattle miscommunication, and Wild Card break to make it 11-10, Mixed.
Wild Card stops the bleeding. Goal from Heath to Reshef. 11-9 Seattle.
El-Salaam owns the point. He gets a sick poach D, catches the turnaround huck, dishes and gets the goal. Seattle break to go up 11-8.
Khaleef with another huge play with a poach layout D and then scores the goal on the other end. 11-8 Ghetto.
Wild Card overthrow. Seattle work it and huck to El-Salaam. They find Houser to break back. Mixed up 10-8.
Ghetto Birds with an upwind break after Wild Card throw away in the end zone. Brad Houser goal.
Seattle goal on a huck from Johnson to Burton. 9-8 Ghetto.
Johnson with a sweet rip to Burton for the hold. Seattle Mixed up 9-8.
Wild Card break out of half to make it 8s.
Ghetto Birds take half 8-7. They will come out on O
Cameron Bailey with the layout D out of the TO & immediately throws a scoober while still on the ground to Kahyee Fong for the goal.
Throwaway by Drew Johnson of Seattle. Wild Card timeout.
Ghetto Birds have trouble handling the pull and immediate turn it. Wild Card with another break on the McInnis goal. Tied at 7's
Wild Card with their third D of the point and this time is able to convert. Big break for Wild Card. 7-6 Seattle leads.
Minneapolis Drag'n Thrust will advance to defend their title against the winner of the Wild Card-Seattle Mixed semis. Game will be at 11 AM
Wild card with another D, but immediately throws it away for the second time this point.
Drescher makes a sick grab on a huck and continues to Hron for the win. 15-12, Drag'n Thrust over CLX.
Wild Cars gets the turn, but can't convert 15 yards out.
Larson comes down with a crazy grab: lays out, macs it, grabs it with the other hand while still on the ground. 14-12, Drag'n.
After turns by both teams, Wild Card holds. 7-5 Seattle.
Another long point but Drag'n fight it out for the hold to go up 14-11.
Wild Cars turn on the goal line. Khaleef El-Saleem with a posterizing sky on a floaty huck and then throws the assist. 7-4 Ghetto Birds.
Brorsen catches the mac on a deep look for the CLX hold. 13-11, Drag'n.
Burton playing really well early for Ghetto. 2 goals 2 assists.

Machine's loss to Madison Club at CHC has been effectively erased with their convincing wins over Bravo, Chain, and Ironside this weekend.
Their last two games proved that when Machine are patient, hit their marks, and make space for each other, they can beat anybody.
Chicago Machine defeat Boston Ironside in the finals of the Pro Flight Finale 13-10. A shaky Saturday is erased by a solid Sunday.
Confused foul call nullified and Machine wins the game on a huck from AJ Nelson!
Another Kapinos huck to Neff. 12-10, Machine. Game point for Chicago.
Geppert monster left-handed layout grab on a 70-yard crossfield flick bomb from Kubalanza! 12-9, Machine.
Lots of big hucks. Wiseman huck to Goose D'd by Garcia. Kapinos rip to Malecek saved by a nice layout grab. Ironside holds. 11-9, Machine.
Kelly gets it back with a huge layout D.
Goose huck deemed not a foul by observer. Disc back to Boston.
Walden Nelson giant layout D.
Machine stay patient until Liu puts up a money backhand huck to AJ Nelson for the hold. Chicago back up 11-8.
Mance unaware of sidelines and is OB. Ironside work it up. Neff finds Kapinos for the hold. 10-8, Machine.
Ironside working well until Garcia miffs an easy swing. Machine takes a TO.
Geppert puts a perfect O-I to Wiseman in a small window. Machine up 10-7.
Malecek rips a backhand dime to Garcia. 9-7, Machine.
Despite good Ironside D, AJ Nelson gets some separation and Goose finds him deep. 9-6, Machine.
No cushion D by Ironside frustrating Machine.
Simmons hits C-Fo for the break. Ironside down 6-8, looking to close the gap.
Long, sloppy point with a handful of turns. But Boston get it near the endzone and burn a TO, looking for the break.
Ironside starts with an easy huck to George Stubbs and continue to Sayre-McCord. 8-5, Machine.
Machine looks thematically similar to GOAT at the PFF last year. They're staying aggressive and continually executing.
Machine runs a zipper. Kapinos is almost there, but AJ Nelson makes a good grab. Chicago takes half on Boston 8-4.
Great Machine D forces an Ironside turn. Goose calls a TO.
Great I-O flick opens up an easy break continuation. Boston plays good D, but Chicago stays patient and punches it in to make it 7-4.
Ironside turning up the D. Machine stack looking a bit sloppy.
Ironside takes what they're given. Rebholz finds Garcia to make it 6-4, Machine.
Machine can't take advantage and have to punt.
Goose massive layout D. Even lost his shorts.
Tight dump D forces an Ironside punt. Machine taking some gutsy shots. I-O floater to Kelly connects. Chicago breaks to go up 6-3.
Liu puts up a beauty to Kraemer who makes a great grab to give Machine the hold. Tight window, but Chicago converts to go up 5-3 .
Another miscue gives Boston an easy break. 4-3, Chicago now only up a break.
Machine miscommunication leads to an easy goal for Ironside. Boston stops the bleeding to make it 4-2, Chicago.
Poeppelman goes HUGE to sky Wallack with help D. After discussion, ruled a D.
Both teams aggressive deep. They've scored two in a row with hucks. 4-1.
Reset mistake for Machine leads to a McNaughton Callahan. Very strange.
Wiseman hucks to Gepper who gets up for the goal. 1-0 hold. Machine o line saying not satisfied.
Shriwise comes down with the game-winner. Machine bests Chain 15-11 to advance to the finals.
Clark finds Joel Wooten to make it 14-11, Machine.
Shriwise comes down with a big sky to make it 14-10. Machine on the verge of advancing.
Sweet help D by AJ Nelson macs right to Taylor. Chain gets the break to make it 13-10, Machine.
Ironside close out 15-7 over GOAT.
Lou finds Joel Wooten to make it 13-9, Machine.
Sloppy point, but Boston get the break. 14-7, Ironside.
Machine earn another break.13-8, Chicago.
Garcia sweet rip to Neff. 13-7, Boston.

Chain make it quick. 11-8, Machine.
Machine hold after a foul on a deep shot. 11-7, Chicago up on Atlanta.

GOAT hold to make it 11-6.

Nice poach D by Machine. They burn a TO.
Chain overthrow Wilson on a deep look. Machine navigates some poaches and hit a nice O-I over the top for the break. 6-3, Chicago.
Ironside is capitalizing on just about every GOAT slip-up. Boston cruising 6-2.
Massive layout help D by Babbitt.
Machine having their way on offense. Chain junk set looked confused. Chicago up 5-3. Atlanta burn a TO.
GOAT missing the mark on O. Ironside notch another easy break. Boston up 5-2. Toronto call a TO.

Ironside up a break on GOAT. Tied at 2s, Boston receiving.
Three of the men's semifinalists have only won two games on the weekend, including their quarters victories.
Mixed finals: Polar Bears vs. CLX. Game starts at 3.
CLX beat Mischief 15-12.
Semis match-ups for men's starting at 1: Chain vs. Machine, GOAT vs. Ironside.
Ironside close out on Doublewide 15-9. Boston is the only team to hold seed in the men's division.
Three big upsets in the quarters for men's. Craziness.
Alexander floaty hammer to the back of the endzone and Lloyd skies Castine for the universe point win! GOAT advances 12-11!
Bravo turn on a huck to Mickle. Machine work it up and punch it for the big upset! Chicago advances on a huge 15-11 win!
Revolver turn near their own endzone. Liu with a nice cross to Joel Wooten for the upset! 13-11, Chain advance!
Spiva comes down with a huck when Joye trips. 12-11, Chain. Revolver trying to force universe.

Fury trouncing Capitals 14-7. SF to receive, looking to close out.

GOAT holds to go up 9-8 on Sockeye.
Watson with a dirty lefty scoober for the Bravo hold. 11-9, Machine.
Machine notches a crucial break to go up 11-8 on Bravo.

Sloppy point between Revolver and Chain. Still 8-7, SF.

Polar Bears annihilating Cosa Nostra 14-5.
CLX up 10-8 on Mischief. Ames about to receive.
Revolver leading Chain 8-7. SF receiving.
Machine holding their advantage over Bravo 8-7. Chicago about to receive.
Sockeye can't convert their break opportunities. GOAT hold. 7s.
Doublewide hold out of half, but trail Ironside 8-4.
Fury take half on Capitals 8-4.

Chain holds. 6-5 Revolver.
Bravo break to even it up at 5s against Machine.
Evangelides sky D leads to a break for Revolver to put them up 6-4 over Chain.
Ironside making it look easy, up 5-2 on Doublewide.
Polar Bears rolling Cosa Nostra 6-2.
Revolver and Chain on serve at 3s. Bravo and Machine locked in at 2s.
Confused GOAT O line coughs it up and Sockeye get their break back. 3s.
Errant throw by Sockeye near their own endzone. GOAT gets an early break to go up 3-1.
Mixed semis match-ups starting at 11: Mischief vs. CLX, Polar Bears vs. Cosa Nostra.
Cosa Nostra handle AMP 12-10 to advance. CLX best Wild Card 15-10.
Wild Card looking for the crazy comeback, down 10-13 and about to pull to CLX.
World (and defending national) champion Drag'n Thrust can't make it out of quarters less than a month later. Nationals is going to be fun.
Polar Bears close it out 15-7. Mischief give up some momentum but finish it up 15-10. Both Southwest teams dominate their way into semis.
AMP break again to tie it at 9s. Polar Bears running away with it 14-7, scoring six out of the seven second half goals against Slow White.
AMP break to make it 8-9. Cosa Nostra still up and about to receive.
Polar Bears stomping Slow White 13-7.
Polar Bears about to pull up 12-7 on Slow White. Cosa Nostra up 9-6 on AMP. Latter game looking a little sloppy.

Men's quarters match-ups: Revolver-Chain, Bravo-Machine, Ironside-Doublewide, Sockeye-GOAT. All games start at 11 a.m. PST tomorrow.
Revolver and Sockeye win their pools, despite both losing to the team that ended up finishing last (GOAT and Chain).
Miscommunication between Yearwood and Lloyd on second throw. Machine punch it to win 14-13. Despite beating Revolver, GOAT finishes last.
Machine and GOAT tied at 13s. Toronto receiving.

Mischief 8-7 Amp. Wild Card 7-5 Polar Bears.
Machine up 7-5 on GOAT at half. Chicago about to receive.
Revolver take half 7-4. Ironside to receive. Surprisingly sloppy game on both sides so far.
Revolver on a 4-0 run, up 6-3 on Ironside.

Teams trade some breaks. Back on serve. Revolver up 4-3, pulling to Ironside.
Some sloppiness on both sides, but Revolver up a break on Ironside, 2-1. SF receiving.
Unreal grab by Sefton to win the game! Sockeye upsets Bravo 13-12.
Bravo stay patient, and Watson finds Westbrook crossfield for the hold. 12s.
Matt Russell skies Mickle for the D. Sockeye work it down for the break to take the lead back, 12-11.

Rehder monster sky over Peterson. Sockeye hold to make it 10-9.
Both O lines hold. 8s with Sockeye receiving.

Sick layout D by Koss on a Lance deep shot.

Muffin putting up some money hucks. 4-3, Machine up and set to receive.

Higgins hits a wide open Boucher deep. 2s.
Teams trade turns, but Machine punch it in with some dirty scoobers and hammers. 2-1, Chicago.
Revolver throw a bad huck, and Machine convert with a huge sky from Wiseman. Chicago start with a break and go up 1-0.
Late update: Bravo handled Doublewide 13-7. All of the Pool B teams have a bye until 1.

Sockeye miscommunication near their own endzone leads to an easy break by Chain to put it back on serve, 7-6. Seattle to receive out of half
Sockeye O have been taking it slower than usual. But great break continuations and smart movement still make it look good. 6-5 Seattle.
Hungry Sockeye D forces Chain to take a TO on offense.
Errant throw on the goal line gives Sockeye their first break at 5-4. Seattle doing a great job of using the whole field.
Fury and Capitals locked in at 3s. Both teams had some chances.
Sockeye O looking clean and assured, not having to work too hard or struggle to punch it in. 3s.
Sockeye and Chain trading O holds at 2s. Both teams had some chances for breaks but couldn't convert.
